<h2>Maricopa County Surplus Funds and Excess Proceeds</h2>

<p>
Each year thousands of homes are foreclosed throughout Maricopa County Arizona. When a foreclosure auction sells a property 
for more than the mortgage balance or liens owed, the remaining money becomes <strong>excess proceeds</strong> or 
<strong>foreclosure surplus funds</strong>.
</p>

<p>
These funds may legally belong to the former property owner, heirs, or other lienholders. Unfortunately many people 
never realize they have money waiting to be claimed.
</p>

<h2>Common Terms Used for Maricopa County Surplus Funds</h2>

<p>
People searching for these funds may use different terms including:
</p>

<ul>

<li>Maricopa County excess proceeds</li>
<li>Maricopa County surplus funds</li>
<li>Maricopa County foreclosure overages</li>
<li>Maricopa County tax sale surplus</li>
<li>Maricopa County unclaimed foreclosure funds</li>
<li>Arizona foreclosure excess proceeds</li>

</ul>

