<h2>Why Surplus Funds Go Unclaimed</h2>

<ul>

<li>Homeowners move after foreclosure</li>
<li>Mail notices are never received</li>
<li>Heirs are unaware the funds exist</li>
<li>The claim process appears complicated</li>

</ul>

<h2>How To Claim Maricopa County Excess Proceeds</h2>

<p>
Claiming foreclosure surplus funds generally requires filing a claim with the court and verifying legal entitlement 
to the funds. Documentation may include proof of ownership, identification, and foreclosure case records.
</p>

<p>
Because the process can be complex, many individuals seek assistance locating and recovering surplus funds.
</p>

